{"key":"processedPost-6201432","value":{"id":6201432,"first":6199297,"last":11885218,"when":1161623017,"utime":"10/23/06 08:03 PM","content":"You guys need to make a distinction between oven or water bath temperature and substrate temperature.  The <i><u>substrate</u></i> needs to be at 140F to 170F for an hour, but not over 1 1/2 hours.  Use a meat thermometer stuck into the middle of the substrate and manipulate whatever you have to in order to achieve the above.  Ovens are horrible for pasteurization because air is a poor at transferring heat.  Water is much better.","title":"Re: My First Oven POO Pasteurization QUICK QUESTION","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}